      <hedline>
        <hl1>CHINA AIR TALKS</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <byline class="print_byline">By Craig S. Smith</byline>
      <byline class="normalized_byline">Smith, Craig S</byline>
      <abstract>
        <p>China Southern Airlines Group is in merger talks with China Northern Airlines Group; China's airline regulator has been pressing 10 airlines under its control to merge into three largest airline groups: Air China, China Eastern Airlines and China Southern Airlines (S)</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>China's largest airline, the China Southern Airlines Group, is in merger talks with the China Northern Airlines Group, Chinese news reports said. China's airline regulator has been pressing the 10 airlines under its control to merge into the three largest airline groups: Air China, China Eastern Airlines and China Southern Airlines.</p>
        <p>Craig S. Smith</p>
      </block>
